# TypeScript

## Strictness

- Avoid `any` and `unknown` - use a proper type/interface, or narrow `unknown` before use
- Avoid non-null assertions (`!`) and `as` casts; if unavoidable, add a short comment saying why
- Annotate return types on exported functions
- Use `type` imports for type-only symbols: `import { type Foo } from "./foo"`

## Naming

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Variables, functions | `camelCase` | `getClientById` |
| Components | `PascalCase` | `QuotationCard` |
| Types, interfaces | `PascalCase` | `QuotationStatus` |
| Constants | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` | `DEMO_PASSWORD` |
| Component files | `kebab-case` | `login-screen.tsx` |
| Util / hook files | `kebab-case` or `camelCase` | `use-app-store.ts` |

## Imports

- Apps import `@repo/ui/*` package exports - not deep paths into `packages/ui/src`
- Never use relative paths to cross a package boundary

## Client components

- `"use client"` on interactive screens, store, navigation, Gluestack provider
- Route `page.tsx` can stay a server component when it only re-exports a client screen

## Error handling

```typescript
// ✅ typed, never swallowed
try {
  return await generateAiDraft(request);
} catch (error: unknown) {
  if (error instanceof AiDraftError) throw error;
  throw new Error("AI draft failed", { cause: error });
}

// ❌ swallowed
try { return await generateAiDraft(request); } catch (e) { return null; }
```

## Shared types

Domain models live in `packages/ui/src/types/models.ts`. Reuse them; don't redeclare.

## Checks

```bash
pnpm typecheck    # from root
```

Fix type errors before finishing; `ignoreBuildErrors` is not a license to ship broken types.
